channel.title: My Java Project- Browser based MMORPG! (In Development. Soon To Be Released)
channel.description:
Hey everybody. I am currently creating a new browser based mmorpg called 'Racing Gears' I have been working on this for about 4 months now. What you do is choose your characters avatar and car. You unlock more cars and avatars as you play the game. There are weapons like smoke screen (blinds other players), Missles (Shoots missles from the front of the car), mines (puts a mine in the road for enemy's to run over), Heat Seeking Missles (Hits the nearest car to you), Oil Slick (shoots oil behind you to cause the enemy to spin out.), and much much more! Also there are tons of upgrades for your vehicle, upgrade you engine, turbo, armor, and cells 4x and your brakes 3x! If you take damage to your care you must repair it. Have up to 8 players in a race. HD Graphics. Over 30 tracks to race! Must sit in the waiting room and wait for atleast one other player b4 you can start a race. Here are some pix:
Choose your ride and avatar [IMG]http://i344.photobucket.com/albums/p348/tekidder_2008/1-3.jpg[/img]
Waiting Room [IMG]http://i344.photobucket.com/albums/p348/tekidder_2008/6-2.jpg[/img]
Weapons [IMG]http://i344.photobucket.com/albums/p348/tekidder_2008/3-2.jpg[/img]
Tires for different terrain (snow, dirt, road ect...) [IMG]http://i344.photobucket.com/albums/p348/tekidder_2008/4-2.jpg[/img]
Line up to start [IMG]http://i344.photobucket.com/albums/p348/tekidder_2008/7-2.jpg[/img]
Unique Maps [IMG]http://i344.photobucket.com/albums/p348/tekidder_2008/8-2.jpg[/img]
Missles (Non-heat seeking) [IMG]http://i344.photobucket.com/albums/p348/tekidder_2008/f0c04002.jpg[/img]
Smoke Screen [IMG]http://i344.photobucket.com/albums/p348/tekidder_2008/9-2.jpg[/img]
Repair your ride [IMG]http://i344.photobucket.com/albums/p348/tekidder_2008/2-2.jpg[/img]
Upgrade your ride [IMG]http://i344.photobucket.com/albums/p348/tekidder_2008/5-1.jpg[/img]
More pix and updates coming soon!
SPACEFIC GAME CACHE: http://uppit.com/v/38tgny6y
*Note Do not extract the game cache. simply save it somewhere. Then when you open the client click file open and open the cache from wherever you saved it to.
Client Download: http://uppit.com/v/K3TXTPYM
*Note Extract this anywhere you want. This will only be singleplayer unless you connect to the network. In order to connect to the network on the client click options, click link at the very bottom, make sure wireless adaptar is checked, then go into the link settings or press (Ctrl+M) In the general tab make sure you click network, set the port to 5738 click the client tab then where it says localhost type: 5.30.48.200 You must connect to my HAMACHI TO PLAY MULTIPLAYER! Hamachi network is Z4SO and the pass is Z4SO
